'''Verruciform xanthoma''' is an uncommon [[Benign tumor|benign]]<ref name="pmid9793968">{{cite journal |author=Leong FJ, Meredith DJ |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the vulva. A case report |journal=[[Pathol. Res. Pract.]] |volume=194 |issue=9 |pages=661–5; discussion 666–7 |year=1998 |pmid=9793968 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> [[lesion]] that has a verruciform ([[wart]]-like) appearance, but it may appear [[Polyp (medicine)|polypoid]], [[papilloma]]tous, or [[Sessility (medicine)|sessile]].<ref name="Andrews">{{cite book |author=James, William D.; Berger, Timothy G.; et al. |title=Andrews' Diseases of the Skin: clinical Dermatology |publisher=Saunders Elsevier |location= |year=2006 |pages= |isbn=0-7216-2921-0 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>{{rp|535}} Usually found on the [[oral mucosa]]<ref name="pmid9537477">{{cite journal |author=Mohsin SK, Lee MW, Amin MB, ''et al.'' |title=Cutaneous verruciform xanthoma: a report of five cases investigating the etiology and nature of xanthomatous cells |journal=[[Am. J. Surg. Pathol.]] |volume=22 |issue=4 |pages=479–87 |year=1998 |month=April |pmid=9537477 |doi= 10.1097/00000478-199804000-00014|url=http://meta.wkhealth.com/pt/pt-core/template-journal/lwwgateway/media/landingpage.htm?issn=0147-5185&volume=22&issue=4&spage=479 |issn=}}</ref> of middle-aged persons, verruciform xanthomas have also been reported on the [[scrotum]] and [[penis]]<ref name="pmid9537477"/><ref name="pmid7702268">{{cite journal |author=Canillot S, Stamm C, Balme B, Perrot H |title=[Verruciform xanthoma of the penis] |language=French |journal=[[Ann Dermatol Venereol]] |volume=121 |issue=5 |pages=404–7 |year=1994 |pmid=7702268 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> of middle-aged to elderly [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[males]].<ref name="pmid2600278">{{cite journal |author=Nakamura S, Kanamori S, Nakayama K, Aoki M |title=Verruciform xanthoma on the scrotum |journal=[[J. Dermatol.]] |volume=16 |issue=5 |pages=397–401 |year=1989 |month=October |pmid=2600278 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> While the most common site is the oral mucosa, lesions that occur elsewhere usually arise on the [[perineum]] or on the skin with some predisposing factor, such as lymphedema or an [[Epidermis (skin)|epidermal]] [[nevus]].<ref name="pmid6468717">{{cite journal |author=Haustein UF |title=[Xanthomatous cells in inflammatory linear verrucous epidermal nevus or nevoid verruciform xanthoma?] |language=German |journal=[[Dermatol Monatsschr]] |volume=170 |issue=7 |pages=475–8 |year=1984 |pmid=6468717 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref>

==Histology==
A distinguishing feature of verruciform xanthoma is the presence of large numbers of [[lipid]]-laden foamy [[histiocyte]]s<ref name="pmid9793968"/><ref name="pmid9537477"/><ref name="pmid14668556">{{cite journal |author=Reich O, Regauer S |title=Recurrent verruciform xanthoma of the vulva |journal=[[Int. J. Gynecol. Pathol.]] |volume=23 |issue=1 |pages=75–7 |year=2004 |month=January |pmid=14668556 |doi=10.1097/01.pgp.0000101143.79462.f7 |url=http://meta.wkhealth.com/pt/pt-core/template-journal/lwwgateway/media/landingpage.htm?issn=0277-1691&volume=23&issue=1&spage=75 |issn=}}</ref> in the lesion, and essentially limited to, the [[connective tissue]] [[wiktionary:Papilla|papillae]] in the lesion.  The lesions are solitary, raised, or polypoid with cup-shaped craters filled with [[parakeratosis|parakeratotic cells]] that blend into [[keratinocyte]]s of an [[acanthosis|acanthotic]] and papillomatous [[Epidermis (skin)|epidermis]]. There is a [[neutrophil]]ic infiltrate of varying intensity between plump parakeratotic cells and keratinocytes, near the surface of the epidermis.<ref name="pmid9537477"/>

==Etiology==
Verruciform xanthoma is most likely not a [[human papillomavirus]] associated lesion and the foam cells in the lesions are most likely derived from the [[monocyte]]—[[macrophage]] lineage.<ref name="pmid16155700">{{cite journal |author=Hu JA, Li YN, Li SY, Ying H |title=[Study of the clinicopathology on verruciform xanthoma of the oral cavity] |language=Chinese |journal=Shanghai Kou Qiang Yi Xue |volume=14 |issue=4 |pages=370–3 |year=2005 |month=August |pmid=16155700 |doi= |url=http://www.omschina.org.cn/sjs/info.asp?id=1737 |issn= |format=}} {{dead link|date=May 2010}}</ref> More research is needed is determine the etiology.

==Epidemiology==
Verruciform xanthoma is uncommon, with a female:male ratio of 1:1.1<ref name="pmid12676251">{{cite journal |author=Philipsen HP, Reichart PA, Takata T, Ogawa I |title=Verruciform xanthoma--biological profile of 282 oral lesions based on a literature survey with nine new cases from Japan |journal=[[Oral Oncol.]] |volume=39 |issue=4 |pages=325–36 |year=2003 |month=June |pmid=12676251 |doi= 10.1016/S1368-8375(02)00088-X|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S136883750200088X |issn=}}</ref>

==Symptoms==
The most common location by far is the [[gingiva]]l margin and other areas of the [[mastication|masticatory]] oral mucosa,<ref name="pmid12676251">{{cite journal |author=Philipsen HP, Reichart PA, Takata T, Ogawa I |title=Verruciform xanthoma--biological profile of 282 oral lesions based on a literature survey with nine new cases from Japan |journal=Oral Oncol. |volume=39 |issue=4 |pages=325–36 |year=2003 |month=June |pmid=12676251 |doi= 10.1016/S1368-8375(02)00088-X|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S136883750200088X |issn=}}</ref> these occur more frequently in the fifth decade of life, and have good prognosis, the treatment of choice for oral VXs is [[Surgery|surgical excision]], and recurrence is rare.<ref name="pmid17339158">{{cite journal |author=Yu CH, Tsai TC, Wang JT, ''et al.'' |title=Oral verruciform xanthoma: a clinicopathologic study of 15 cases |journal=J. Formos. Med. Assoc. |volume=106 |issue=2 |pages=141–7 |year=2007 |month=February |pmid=17339158 |doi= 10.1016/S0929-6646(09)60230-8|url=http://ajws.elsevier.com/ajws_pubmed/pubmed_switch.asp?journal_issn=0929-6646&art_pub_year=2007&art_pub_month=02&art_pub_vol=106&art_sp=141 |issn= |format=}} {{dead link|date=May 2010}}</ref>

The condition can affect other organs of body, such as the [[penis]],<ref name="pmid9412234">{{cite journal |author=Torrecilla Ortíz C, Marco Pérez LM, Dinares Prat J, Autonell J |title=[Verruciform xanthoma of the penis] |language=Spanish; Castilian |journal=[[Actas Urol Esp]] |volume=21 |issue=8 |pages=797–9 |year=1997 |month=September |pmid=9412234 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> [[vulva]],<ref name="pmid9793968"/><ref name="pmid14668556"/><ref name="pmid2807284">{{cite journal |author=de Rosa G, Barra E, Gentile R, Boscaino A, Di Prisco B, Ayala F |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the vulva: case report |journal=[[Genitourin Med]] |volume=65 |issue=4 |pages=252–4 |year=1989 |month=August |pmid=2807284 |pmc=1194362 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> and can occur in [[Anus|anal]] region,<ref name="pmid7386619">{{cite journal |author=Griffel B, Cordoba M |title=Verruciform xanthoma in the anal region |journal=[[Am J Proctol Gastroenterol Colon Rectal Surg]] |volume=31 |issue=4 |pages=24–5 |year=1980 |month=April |pmid=7386619 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> [[Human nose|nose]],<ref name="pmid10341929">{{cite journal |author=Than T, Birch PJ, Dawes PJ |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the nose |journal=[[J Laryngol Otol]] |volume=113 |issue=1 |pages=79–81 |year=1999 |month=January |pmid=10341929 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref><ref name="pmid3072323">{{cite journal |author=Landthaler M, Manzini BM, Spornraft P, Braun-Falco O |title=[The disease picture of verruciform xanthoma] |language=German |journal=[[Hautarzt]] |volume=39 |issue=11 |pages=727–30 |year=1988 |month=November |pmid=3072323 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref> the [[ear]],<ref name="pmid1329573">{{cite journal |author=Jensen JL, Liao SY, Jeffes EW |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the ear with coexisting epidermal dysplasia |journal=[[Am J Dermatopathol]] |volume=14 |issue=5 |pages=426–30 |year=1992 |month=October |pmid=1329573 |doi= 10.1097/00000372-199210000-00009|url= |issn=}}</ref> lower extremity,<ref name="pmid3312319">{{cite journal |author=Chyu J, Medenica M, Whitney DH |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the lower extremity--report of a case and review of literature |journal=[[J. Am. Acad. Dermatol.]] |volume=17 |issue=4 |pages=695–8 |year=1987 |month=October |pmid=3312319 |doi= 10.1016/S0190-9622(87)80466-8|url= |issn=}}</ref> [[scrotum]].<ref name="pmid2600278"/><ref name="pmid3914496">{{cite journal |author=Shindo Y, Mikoshiba H, Okamoto K, Morohashi M |title=Verruciform xanthoma of the scrotum |journal=[[J. Dermatol.]] |volume=12 |issue=5 |pages=443–8 |year=1985 |month=October |pmid=3914496 |doi= |url= |issn=}}</ref>

==Differential diagnosis==
[[Differential diagnosis]] includes [[seborrheic keratosis]], [[verruca simplex]], [[condyloma acuminatum]], [[granular cell myoblastoma]], [[vulvar intraepithelial neoplasia]], [[bowenoid papulosis]], [[erythroplasia of Queyrat]], and [[verrucous carcinoma]]<ref name="pmid14668556"/>

==Treatment==
Surgical excision is the treatment of choice.<ref name="pmid10640929">{{cite journal |author=Connolly SB, Lewis EJ, Lindholm JS, Zelickson BD, Zachary CB, Tope WD |title=Management of cutaneous verruciform xanthoma |journal=[[J. Am. Acad. Dermatol.]] |volume=42 |issue=2 Pt 2 |pages=343–7 |year=2000 |month=February |pmid=10640929 |doi= 10.1016/S0190-9622(00)90108-7|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0190-9622(00)90108-7 |issn=}}</ref>

